<br>
Yes, root would give us SOME defense.<br>
<br>
Yes, I personally would also use it to make chain casting pets easier.<br>
<br>
Yes, I would use it to split easiliy soloable mobs.<br>
<br>
<br>
I do not see anything wrong with any of this.  Root can break at any time. It balances itself.  On a financial standpoint, root for mages will help make mages go through time time needed to get impoved reclaim energy = more money for verant anyway, and IMO not unbalancing in the least.<br>
<br>
I am sick of:<br>
<br>
A) having to die or gate in JAGGEDPINE FOREST gnoll caves because I had two mobs on me while every other class that can solo in there doesn't have to.<br>
<br>
B) Having to die or gate because I said &quot;/pet gert lost&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
As of right now, no bull, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> my level 55 non-twinked rogue can solo slightly better than my level 55 mage</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  <br>
<br>
As of right now, the best exp I can find is in twilight sea, the twilight armor quest givers and two guards. 11 spawns in all, all in the same area, 20 minute spawn time.  In the 20 minutes, my mage has trouble finishing 10 off. My rogue can do all 11 solo with time to spare.<br>
<br>
My rogue doesn't that that great of equipment, either. The only major factor would be my mrylokar's BP. Hardly a high-end item these days. It's not that rogues are overpowered, it's that the only mobs i can reliably kill (at least as well as any other casting class) are these 11 light blue quest npcs.<br>
<br>
My mage CAN however solo bigger mobs. The only problem is, I can't single pull.  everywhere else I go, I am guaronteed an add within an hour, or even the first pull.<br>
<br>
Warriors are soloing in sebilis.  WARRIORS! I could never solo in there because I'd have to bind myself outside in case of an add. It's not a challenge. It's simply NOT fun. It's a challenge when there's tactics involed. It's not a challenge when it's purely random.<br>
<br>
The only ways i can think of to solve these problems is root and 2 second cast time pets. As far as I can see, the least unbalancing of the two would be the root.<br>
<br>
1) Root would increase power in soloing and defense and nothing else. It doesn't help kill uber mobs faster and we'd never be the crowd control of a raid. On occasion, we might be the rooter of an exp group.<br>
<br>
2) Root costs mana. We can either chain cast without a root to save mana, or we can spend 100-200 mana on a root to make chaining safely a little less mana efficient.<br>
<br>
3) Root breaks. This in itself is a balancing factor.<br>
<br>
4) a 2 second cast time pet means more pets faster which means slightly faster kills.  While I doubt this would make much of a difference in the long run, it's more to test.<br>
<br>
5) a 2 second cast time pet doesn't cost us any more mana. It's just plain faster casting. there's no balancing factor.<br>
<br>
<br>
as for comments from lawrence poe...  Does he even still work there? I could come up with numerous quotes from abashi that aren't true anymore, too. Would take me 5 minutes on the castersrealm news archive.<br>
<br>
I think after this much time, verant could at least test root with mages and see how things go. Try to use it as an exploit and see what the REAL effect is. I believe that in practice it will be powerful, but not overpowering.<br>
<br>
And if it is deemed overpowered by verant AFTER testing, I will be satisfied that I am wrong. Otherwise, I will always believe that mages should have root, period.<br>
